Preconditions:
    • The user has a computer with Python and the requests library installed.
    • The user has access to the JSONPlaceholder API (https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/).
Test Steps:
    1. Import the requests library.
    2. Send a GET request to the following endpoint: https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1
    3. Verify that the response code is 200 (OK).
    4. Verify that the response headers contain the "content-type" header with a value of
    "application/json; charset=utf-8".
    5. Verify that the response body contains a "userId" field with a value of 1.
    6. Verify that the response body contains a "title" field with a non-empty value.
    7. Verify that the response body contains a "body" field with a non-empty value.
Expected Results:
    • The response code is 200 (OK).
    • The response headers contain the "content-type" header with a value of "application/json;
    charset=utf-8".
    • The response body contains a "userId" field with a value of 1.
    • The response body contains a "title" field with a non-empty value.
    • The response body contains a "body" field with a non-empty value.